article.description: Isaiah Whitehead scored 22 points and Seton Hall beat Creighton 75-65 on Saturday.
article.headline: Whitehead scores 22 points, Seton Hall beats Creighton 75-65
article.linkText: Whitehead scores 22 points, Seton Hall beats Creighton 75-65
article.story: OMAHA, Neb. -- Isaiah Whitehead scored 22 points and Seton Hall beat Creighton 75-65 on Saturday. Whitehead was 9 of 17 from the field and made 4 of 6 3-point attempts while notching six assists for the Pirates (15-6, 5-4 Big East). Desi Rodriguez scored 14 points with 10 assists, Angel Delgado had 13 points and grabbed 12 boards and Ismael Sanogo added 12 points. James Milliken led Creighton (14-8, 5-4) with 21 points, while Maurice Watson Jr. added 14 points and six assists. The Bluejays made just 6 of 23 (26 percent) from beyond the arc and were outrebounded 46-27. Seton Hall scored the last seven points of the first half and led 40-27 at the break. The lead grew to 54-32 in the first 3:12 of the second half -- with Rodriguez' 3-pointer capping a 14-5 run -- before Creighton called timeout. The Bluejays cut it to 10 with 5:42 left, but got no closer.
